net.sf.mpxj.reader

Interface ProjectReader

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractProjectFileReader, AbstractProjectReader, AbstractProjectStreamReader, AstaFileReader, AstaJdbcReader, AstaMdbReader, AstaSqliteReader, AstaTextFileReader, ConceptDrawProjectReader, FastTrackReader, GanttDesignerReader, GanttProjectReader, MerlinReader, MPDDatabaseReader, MPDFileReader, MPPReader, MPXReader, MSPDIReader, P3DatabaseReader, P3PRXFileReader, PhoenixReader, PlannerReader, PrimaveraDatabaseFileReader, PrimaveraDatabaseReader, PrimaveraPMFileReader, PrimaveraXERFileReader, ProjectCommanderReader, ProjectLibreReader, SageReader, SDEFReader, SureTrakDatabaseReader, SureTrakSTXFileReader, SynchroReader, TurboProjectReader, UniversalProjectReader

    public interface ProjectReader
    This interface is implemented by all classes which can read project files of any type and generate an ProjectFile instance from the contents of the file.

    • Method Detail

      • setProperties

        ProjectReader setProperties(Properties props)
        Pass a set of Properties to allow the behavior of a reader to be configured. This provides an alternative to calling individual setter methods to set the values of the properties you need to configure.

        NOTE: currently this only supports Boolean properties.

        Properties are passed in this form: <class name>.<property name>=<property value>. This method will ignore any properties which are not intended for the current reader class. Here's an example: 

         net.sf.mpxj.phoenix.PhoenixReader.UseActivityCodesForTaskHierarchy=true
        Parameters:
        props - properties to set
        Returns:
        current ProjectReader instance to allow method chaining

      • setCharset

        void setCharset(Charset charset)
        Some readers will be sensitive to the encoding of the file they are reading. If this is applicable, this method can be called to set the encoding to use when reading a file.
        Parameters:
        charset - encoding to use when reading a file
